      <hedline>
        <hl1>Car Kills Man on Sidewalk; Driver Accused of Homicide</hl1>
      </hedline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>LEAD: A 36-year-old Bronx man was killed instantly last night when a car driven by a drunken driver mounted the sidewalk and struck him, the police reported.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>LEAD: A 36-year-old Bronx man was killed instantly last night when a car driven by a drunken driver mounted the sidewalk and struck him, the police reported.</p>
        <p>A 36-year-old Bronx man was killed instantly last night when a car driven by a drunken driver mounted the sidewalk and struck him, the police reported.</p>
        <p>The victim, Angel Tizzaro of 2512 University Avenue, had parked his car and got out at 8:30 P.M. on Sedgwick Avenue at 180th Street in Morris Heights to urinate, a police spokesman said.</p>
        <p>A car driven by Raul Irizarry, 31, of 1044 St. John's Avenue, struck Mr. Tizzaro as he stood on the sidewalk, knocking him over a fence.</p>
        <p>Mr. Irizarry was charged with vehicular homicide and driving while intoxicated, the police said.</p>
      </block>
